> 
> I have run into a wierd problem with the assertEquals.
> 
> 
> The following statements work properly in my code...
> expected.equals(actual) 
> assertTrue(expect.equals(actual)) 
> 
> The following statement does not...
> assertEquals(expected,actual);

asserEquals(o1, o2) eventually executes o2.equals(o1). That's what happened
in an earlier JUnit version.
Thus, if your implementation of equals() is not symmetric you might run into
that problem. According to the Java spec equals(Object) must always be
symmetric.

Johannes
